le="margin-top:7px;margin-bottom:3px">授業形態</div></td><td width="50" align="center"><div style="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:3px">演習</div></td></tr><tr><td width="100" align="center" bgcolor="lightsteelblue"><div style="margin-top:7px;margin-bottom:3px">授業実施方法</div></td><td colspan=3 width="450" align="left"><div style="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:3px">&nbsp;&nbsp&#9744対面&nbsp;&nbsp&#9745オンデマンド&nbsp;&nbsp&#9744同時双方向<br></div></td></tr><tr><td colspan="4" width="580"><div style="margin:10px 3px 3px 3px;padding-top:6px;padding-bottom:3px;padding-left:7px;background-color:lightsteelblue">ディプロマ・ポリシーとの対応</div><div style="margin:10px">&#9744&nbsp1.&nbsp人間、文化、社会の課題を技術的観点から理解・考察する能力<br>&#9745&nbsp2.&nbsp広い範囲の工学的知識と数理的理解<br>&#9744&nbsp3.&nbsp様々な研究者・技術者と意見を交わすことのできるコミュニケーション力<br>&#9745&nbsp4.&nbsp課題に対して適切なアプローチを計画し、解決する問題解決力<br>&#9745&nbsp5.&nbsp工学の高度な知識・技術とこれを現実課題に適用し解決する能力<br></div></td></tr><tr><td colspan="4" width="580"><div style="margin:10px 3px 3px 3px;padding-top:6px;padding-bottom:3px;padding-left:7px;background-color:lightsteelblue">授業の目的・達成目標</div><div style="margin:10px"><p><strong>Purpose of class</strong></p>
<p>This class aims to study basic technology of multimedia communications.</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>Achievement goal</strong></p>
<p>-To understand temporal structure of media and concept of QoS (Quality of Service) for multimedia communications</p>
<p>-To understand basics of upper-layer communication protocols</p>
<p>-To understand basic techniques of QoS control for achieving high quality of user experience (QoE: Quality of Experience)</p></div><div style="margin:20px 3px 3px 3px;padding-top:6px;padding-bottom:3px;padding-left:7px;background-color:lightsteelblue">授業計画</div><div style="margin:10px"><p>1. Examples of multimedia communications: multimedia conferencing, remote teaching, voice over IP, networked games, networked virtual environments, etc.</p>
<p>2. Multimedia: Definition and types of media, information volume and compression for each type of media, advantages of multimedia communications</p>
<p>3. Multimedia QoS (Quality of Service): QoS, QoS of audio and video, QoS degradation factors, human perception characteristics, QoS mapping</p>
<p> [Achievement goal for 1 to 3] To understand what media is; to understand that in multimedia, multiple media are temporally related to each other; to understand requirements of QoS for multimedia communications</p>
<p>4. &amp; 5.  QoE (Quality of Experience) assessment and QoS control: Subjective assessment and objective assessment, traffic control (video dynamic resolution control, adaptive dead-reckoning etc.), error control, media synchronization control (intra-stream, inter-stream, and group synchronization control), media synchronization control techniques (basic control, preventive control, reactive control, common control), causality control, consistency control, adaptive reaction force control, adaptive output timing of olfactory media, CPU load control, integrated QoS control, etc.</p>
<p>[Achievement goal for 4 and 5]</p>
<p>To understand necessities of QoS mapping; to understand QoE assessment methods, to understand techniques of application-level QoS control for high-quality QoE</p>
<p>6. &amp; 7. Internet and transport/application protocol: Protocol structure, client-server model, peer-to-peer model, inter-process communication using sockets, outline of TCP/UDP, RTP/RTCP (transport protocols for real-time media transfer), remote login (TELNET), file transfer (FTP), email (SMTP, POP3, IMAP, MIME), WWW (HTTP), etc.</p>
<p>[Achievement goal for 6 and 7]</p>
<p>To learn techniques of communication programs with TCP and UDP; to understand the basics of upper-layer protocol for multimedia communications</p>
<p>8. Examination, confirmation of understanding, summary</p></div><div style="margin:20px 3px 3px 3px;padding-top:6px;padding-bottom:3px;padding-left:7px;background-color:lightsteelblue">成績評価の方法</div><div style="margin:10px"><p>Examination and/or report (100%)</p></div><div style="margin:20px 3px 3px 3px;padding-top:6px;padding-bottom:3px;padding-left:7px;background-color:lightsteelblue">成績評価の基準</div><div style="margin:10px">秀　 達成目標を超えた成果を上げている　100点～90点<br>優　 達成目標に十分達している　　　　　89点～80点<br>良　 達成目標に達している　　　　　　　79点～70点<br>可　 達成目標に概ね達している　　　　　69点～60点<br>不可 達成目標に達していない　　　　　　59点以下<br><p>Evaluation will be made based on whether each goal can be achieved or not.</p>
<p>How high achievement level can be reached is determined by examination and/or report.</p></div><div style="margin:20px 3px 3px 3px;padding-top:6px;padding-bottom:3px;padding-left:7px;background-color:lightsteelblue">事前・事後学修等の指示及び履修にあたっての注意事項</div><div style="margin:10px"><p>Having knowledge of computer networks is desirable.</p></div><div style="margin:20px 3px 3px 3px;padding-top:6px;padding-bottom:3px;padding-left:7px;background-color:lightsteelblue">教科書</div><div style="margin:10px">Necessary documents will be uploaded on Moodle (or distributed by email) before each lesson.<br></div><div style="margin:20px 3px 3px 3px;padding-top:6px;padding-bottom:3px;padding-left:7px;background-color:lightsteelblue">参考書</div><div style="margin:10px"></div><div style="margin:20px 3px 3px 3px;padding-top:6px;padding-bottom:3px;padding-left:7px;background-color:lightsteelblue">オフィスアワー</div><div style="margin:10px"><p id="yui_3_17_2_1_1517193280025_66">Any time. Students must contact the lecturer in advance via email etc.</p>
